[00:37] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'now, and our goal today is the same as it was when we first started the company, and that\'s building great video infrastructure. Historically, that\'s meant making sure we are fast as hell at getting a video, making it playable, and making sure that'

[00:49] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'playback experience is amazing. Obviously, we have to make sure the video plays well on every device on any connection speed, but it also meant building a lot of great features like storyboards, thumbnail previews, animations, all of these things that'

[01:01] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'help build a richer playback experience for the end user. We built all those features for the people building video and watching video, but it turns out that robots really like those features, too. And suddenly, you can get amazing features like content moderation,'

[01:15] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'summarization, tagging, all these sorts of things that our customers have been asking about and talking about or building themselves for years. &gt;&gt; [music] &gt;&gt; With Mux robots enabled on your account, you\'ll find a new robot section in the'

[01:28] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'dashboard. Mux robots brings AI workflows directly into your video pipeline. Instead of wiring together separate tools for video understanding, [music] you can run the jobs right inside of Mux and get structured output back.'

[01:40] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: '&gt;&gt; [music] &gt;&gt; When you create a new job, you can choose from a set of workflows depending on what you\'re trying to do. That includes things like summarization, moderation, translation, question answering, chapters, and key moments. For now, more to come.'

[01:53] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'To kick things off, we\'ll run one of the most basic and useful jobs, summarize. [music] When the job runs, you\'ll get events and webhooks, and you can also see the output right here in the dashboard. So, what you see here is a title, you\'ve got'

[02:05] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'a bunch of tags, and then a description that accurately puts us as two men sitting together in a small curved hot tub completely normally. You can also ask yes or no questions about the video and get results in'

[02:17] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'structured output, as well. In this case, we asked, "Are the bros in the hot tub at least 5 ft apart?" And the answer is confidently yes. We use this one a lot internally as another step of moderation to moderate'

[02:29] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'very specific types of content that we know people are abusing the platform for. So, when we start identifying those, we say, "Is this that piece of content?" And if it says yes, [music] we flag that to handle it later. One of my favorite features in Mux'

[02:42] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'robots is key moments. That allows you to say, "Okay, what are the parts of a video that I should use to make clips from or create a preview for a piece of content in front of a paywall." So, we ran key moments for a classic'

